# Content Strategy Guidelines

## Content Creation Standards

### Blog Post Structure
- **Filename format**: `YYYY-MM-DD-title.html.md` in `source/`
- **Required frontmatter**: title, date, tags
- **Optional frontmatter**: layout (defaults to post), reply (for response posts)
- **Excerpt separator**: Use `<!-- more //-->` for post previews
- **Heading hierarchy**: Start with H2, maintain logical structure

### Frontmatter Patterns
```yaml
---
title: "Descriptive Title"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
tags:
  - tag1
  - tag2
layout: post  # Optional, defaults to blog layout
reply:        # Optional, for response posts
  url: https://example.com
  reply_title: "Original Post Title"
---
```

### Tag Management
- **Tag limits**: 3-5 tags per post maximum
- **Tag consistency**: Use established taxonomy from existing posts
- **Tag format**: Lowercase, hyphenated for multi-word tags
- **Tag purpose**: Facilitate content discovery and organization

## Brand Voice and Editorial Standards

### Writing Guidelines
- **Tone**: Professional yet warm and conversational
- **Voice characteristics**: Authentic, curious, thoughtful, clever, relatable
- **Approach**: Minimal, grounded, personal digital journal style
- **Balance**: Approachable expertise - knowledgeable without being intimidating

### Content Themes and Focus
- **Primary topics**: Technology, parenting, productivity, personal development
- **Content style**: Thoughtful reflections and experimental insights
- **Narrative approach**: Personal experiences with broader applications
- **Technical content**: Accessible explanations with practical examples

## Site Information Architecture

### Navigation Structure
```
Home | Writing | Series | About | Contact
```

### Content Hierarchy and Priorities
1. **Blog/Journal entries** (primary content)
2. **About page** (personal and professional context)
3. **Projects/Series section** (multi-part content organization)
4. **Contact form** (connection facilitation)
5. **Archive/Tags/Topics** (content discovery)

### Homepage Content Strategy
- **Intro section**: Brief welcome message or current focus
- **Recent posts**: Reverse chronological listing with previews
- **Navigation**: Clear paths to main content sections
- **Engagement**: Subtle calls to action for deeper exploration

## Series and Project Organization

### Series Content Structure
- **Series landing pages**: Introduction and sequential post index
- **Post navigation**: Clear next/previous within series
- **Progress indicators**: Show completion status for multi-part content
- **Series badges**: Visual identification in post headers

### Project Documentation Patterns
- **Project scope**: Clear description of goals and outcomes
- **Process documentation**: Steps, decisions, and lessons learned
- **Resource sharing**: Tools, references, and helpful materials
- **Follow-up content**: Updates, iterations, and refined insights

## Content Quality and Editorial Standards

### Editorial Guidelines
- **Clarity**: Write for understanding, not impressiveness
- **Authenticity**: Share genuine experiences and perspectives
- **Value**: Provide actionable insights or meaningful reflection
- **Completeness**: Finish thoughts and provide sufficient context

### Technical Content Standards
- **Accuracy**: Verify technical information and provide sources
- **Accessibility**: Explain technical concepts for general audience
- **Examples**: Include practical, working examples when relevant
- **Updates**: Note when technical content may become outdated

## SEO and Content Discoverability

### On-Page SEO Practices
- **Title optimization**: Descriptive, search-friendly titles under 60 characters
- **Meta descriptions**: Compelling summaries for social sharing
- **Internal linking**: Connect related posts and topics naturally
- **Image optimization**: Descriptive alt text and meaningful file names

### Content Discoverability Strategy
- **Tag strategy**: Consistent taxonomy for topic exploration
- **Series organization**: Logical grouping of related content
- **Cross-referencing**: Link to related posts and external resources
- **Archive structure**: Year-based and topic-based navigation

## Responsive Content and Accessibility

### Multi-Device Content Considerations
- **Reading experience**: Optimized for mobile and desktop consumption
- **Content length**: Appropriate for various reading contexts and attention spans
- **Visual hierarchy**: Clear structure that works across screen sizes
- **Navigation usability**: Touch-friendly interfaces for mobile users

### Accessibility Standards
- **Alt text**: Descriptive text for all images that convey meaning
- **Heading structure**: Logical H1-H6 hierarchy for screen readers
- **Link context**: Descriptive link text and clear external link indication
- **Readability**: Use clear language and appropriate contrast

## Content Maintenance and Version Control

### Regular Content Review
- **Link validation**: Check for broken internal and external links
- **Content freshness**: Update outdated information when relevant
- **Tag cleanup**: Maintain consistent taxonomy and remove unused tags
- **Archive organization**: Ensure historical content remains discoverable

### Version Control Integration
- **Git changelog**: Automatic tracking of content changes via post layout
- **Update documentation**: Note significant revisions in git history
- **Content versioning**: Track major updates to evergreen content
- **Editorial notes**: Document reasoning for significant changes

## Integration with Design and Technical Systems

### Design System Alignment
- **Typography hierarchy**: Follow design system specifications for readability
- **Content width**: Maintain 800px maximum width for optimal reading
- **Spacing**: Use design system spacing grid for content sections
- **Visual consistency**: Maintain brand alignment across all content

### Template and Technical Integration
- **Post layout**: Use established post template patterns consistently
- **Responsive design**: Ensure content works across design system breakpoints
- **Component usage**: Leverage design system components appropriately
- **Performance**: Consider content impact on site loading and navigation

